### PoMiniGames API — REST Client
### Usage: open this file in VS Code with the REST Client extension
### or in JetBrains Rider's HTTP Client.

@baseUrl = http://localhost:5000
@game = tictactoe
@player = Player1

# ─── Health ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### Liveness probe
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/health/ping

###

### Structured health report
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/health

###

### Diagnostic configuration dump (sensitive values masked)
GET {{baseUrl}}/diag

###

# ─── OpenAPI / Scalar ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### OpenAPI spec (JSON)
GET {{baseUrl}}/openapi/v1.json

###

### Scalar interactive docs
GET {{baseUrl}}/scalar/v1

###

# ─── Player Statistics ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### Get player stats
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/{{game}}/players/{{player}}/stats

###

### Save player stats
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/{{game}}/players/{{player}}/stats
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "easy":   { "wins": 5, "losses": 2, "draws": 1, "totalGames": 8, "winStreak": 3 },
  "medium": { "wins": 2, "losses": 4, "draws": 0, "totalGames": 6, "winStreak": 1 },
  "hard":   { "wins": 0, "losses": 1, "draws": 0, "totalGames": 1, "winStreak": 0 }
}

###

# ─── Leaderboard ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### Leaderboard — top 10 tictactoe players
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/tictactoe/statistics/leaderboard?limit=10

###

### Leaderboard — top 5 connectfive players
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/connectfive/statistics/leaderboard?limit=5

###

### All statistics for tictactoe
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/tictactoe/statistics/all

###

### All statistics for connectfive
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/connectfive/statistics/all

###
